1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 2372, Page 5, Section 190.098, Lines
2 24-31, by deleting said lines and inserting in lieu thereof the following:
3
4 "supervisory standards established by the medical director. A community paramedic shall
5 provide services of a health care plan if the plan has been developed by the patient's physician or
6 by an advanced practice registered nurse through a collaborative practice arrangement with a
7 physician or a physician assistant through a collaborative practice arrangement with a physician
8 and there is no duplication of services to the patient from another provider."; and
9
10 Further amend said bill, Page 12, Section 195.417, Line 62, by inserting after said line the
11 following:
12
13 "(5) The fees required under this subsection shall be assessed against each manufacturer
14 solely on the basis of sales transactions involving that manufacturer's own compounds, mixtures,
15 or preparations sold in or into the state. No manufacturer shall be assessed fees based upon
16 transactions attributable to the compounds, mixtures, or preparations of any other
17 manufacturer."; and
18
19 Further amend said bill, Page 55, Section 376.1765, Line 16, by inserting after said section and
20 line the following:
21
22 "407.3007. 1. As used in this section, the following terms mean:
23 (1) "Artificial intelligence" or "AI":
24 (a) Any artificial system that performs tasks under varying and unpredictable
25 circumstances without significant human oversight or that can learn from experience and
26 improve performance when exposed to data sets;
27 (b) An artificial system developed in computer software, physical hardware, or other
28 computer systems that solves tasks requiring human-like perception, cognition, planning,
29 learning, communication, or physical action;
30 (c) An artificial system designed to think or act like a human, including cognitive
31 architectures and neural networks;
32 (d) A set of techniques, including machine learning, that is designed to approximate a
Action Taken___________________________________________ Date __________________
