5868H03.35H
1 cognitive task; or
2 (e) An artificial system designed to act rationally, including an intelligent software agent
3 or embodied robot that achieves goals using perception, planning, reasoning, learning,
4 communicating, decision-making, and acting;
5 (2) "Mental health professional", the same as defined in section 632.005. The term
6 "mental health professional" shall also include any person licensed in a profession regulated
7 under chapter 337.
8 2. Any person or entity that develops or deploys artificial intelligence in the state shall
9 not advertise or represent to the public that the AI is or is able to act as a mental health
10 professional or is capable of providing therapy services, psychotherapy services, or a mental
11 health diagnosis.
12 3. Any violation of this section shall be considered an unlawful practice under the
13 Missouri merchandising practices act under this chapter.
14 4. The attorney general shall enforce the provisions of this section. Any individual may
15 report violations of this section to the attorney general. If the attorney general finds that a
16 violation occurred, the attorney general shall commence a civil action in a court of competent
17 jurisdiction. If the court finds that a violation occurred, the court may grant damages, civil
18 penalties, injunctive relief, attorney's fees, and any such other relief the court finds appropriate.
19 Notwithstanding section 407.100 to the contrary, civil penalties shall be as follows:
20 (1) Ten thousand dollars for the first violation; or
21 (2) Twenty thousand dollars for any subsequent violation."; and
22
23 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
24 accordingly.
